id: monica-settings-permissions
title: Fixed settings saves so pre-existing files and directories regain restrictive POSIX modes
description: Secure mode options only affect newly created settings paths; existing permissive paths can remain exposed after save.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: credentials,filesystem,security,settings
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:59:37.486Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T17:27:13.790Z"
deadline: "2026-07-19T16:59:37.486Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-16T17:19:32.368Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Existing settings directory is repaired to 0700; existing or new settings file is 0600 after save; Windows behavior remains supported; tests use isolated temp paths
definition_of_ready: Current fs mkdir/write mode semantics and audit expectations are reviewed.
parent: monica-security-modernization
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 95
sprint: 2026-07-security-modernization
release: next
reporter: Source security audit
severity: high
environment: local user settings filesystem
repro_steps: "Create settings directory/file with permissive mode, call saveSettings, and inspect mode."
resolution: Added private-directory and private-file write helpers that repair POSIX modes to 0700 and 0600 on every save while retaining Windows compatibility.
expected_result: Existing and new settings paths are private after save.
actual_result: Isolated temporary-path tests prove permissive modes are repaired; the full test suite and platform-safe branches pass.
affected_version: 2026.3.6-2
component: settings-storage
regression: false
customer_impact: Local API credentials may retain overly broad read permissions.
